    "The CBS module consists of three components: convolution blocks, batch normalization process (BN), and SiLU activation function (sigmoid-weighted linear unit activation function) (Fig. 5).",
    "The ELAN module comprises multiple CBS modules that ensure the input and output feature sizes remain unchanged.",
    "By guiding the computational blocks of different feature groups to learn various features, the network's learning capacity is enhanced while preserving the integrity of the original gradient path (Fig. 5).",
    "The MP1 module is divided into two branches specifically an upper branch and a lower branch and consisting of CBS modules and the max pooling (MaxPool) layer (Fig. 4).",
    "In this module, the upper branch utilizes MaxPool to capture the maximum value information from small local areas, while the CBS modules in the lower branch extract all valuable information from small local areas."
